This is my second surf map. Again, I made it because a clanmate told me to and also because I was bored. The way I personally view this map is something along the lines of a surf_skyscraper in that it's more about the combat than the long surf sessions. This map is really free form in that I did not create any death fields, so a player can hop from ramp to ramp at will (permitting they have the speed). Therefore, a player can chase down another for the kill.

Credits:
The map was made entirely by me, BANORRACHY. Testing and refining suggestions were givin thanks to my clanmates. Marksticked looked at it one time really quickly for the heck of it. Sonic was my inspiration for some odd reason. And my thanks go out to Sh!zz for no reason in particular.

If you're curious as to how I made them, or have any other questions, my email is petfield@gmail.com

Also, the map is decompile protected.

**v3 fixes/changes**
-made it so you cant camp the platform before the lock is broken: it hurts you if you do and after the lock is broken, everyone on stage 3 is teleported to the tunnel that leads to stage 3, the guy who broke the lock has a 1 sec head start on everyone else.
-added light to the jail which is triggered by the wall lowering button
-added another metal piece to the launcher so you cant be shot while getting ready to be launched. 
-Added a timer, after 5:15 secs everyone alive will automatically be sent to jail

**6/20/08**
-Fixed a rogue spawn point
-Reduced the time limit from 5:15 secs to 4:15 secs
***********************

**v2 fixes/changes**
-Added hdr
-Changed the third stage, Made it easier to get to the lock, hopefully, to shorten long round times. 
-Added teleports for the awpers on the third stage, you can now go back to a previous stage by jumping on the stage indicator lights.
-Fixed the drop tunnel on the first stage, people were getting stuck inside.
-Added lights to jail
-Changed the laser in jail
-Various touchups
*************************

**v1 fixes**
-Fixed the bug that made it so players were able to mess up the awp/sk337 rotation
-Made it less likely for someone to get stuck in the launcher
**************

-Each Team takes turns awping or sk337ing round per round!!

-Awpers try to stop the surfers!

-First surfer to the end wins ;)

-Laser Operation: Pressing E on the end control panel will activate the laser. User WSAD to control the lasers movement, and left click to shoot!

-Light system: For the awpers you will see 3 lights, Green/Yellow/Red. Green. These lights represent the progress of the surfers. If a surfer makes it to stage 2, the yellow light will turn on. If they make it to stage 3 the Red light will turn on.

-Stage 3: In order to unlock the end, surfer will have to pass through the lock. Afterward the last doorway will be opened.

*********
WARNING: The end laser has been known to crash some clients on certain servers running odd settings. If this is so, I recommend not using the laser. This will NOT crash the server, but the user using the laser.Again, this only happens on some servers. In addition spamming E on the laser activation button Hasbeen known to cause the same problem.
*********

**NOBLOCK REQUIRED** A simple map I made the other day. CT guards the targets whilst T shoots the CT or the targets. Ts start with shotguns+ammo, CT have free awps/p90 + buyzone. Each target is connected to the CTs floor next to it, if all the floors are destroyed then CT are left exposed with no where to hide and get owned. Mass speed = oorange error, I know, but it is harmless. +no fall damage and unprotected map. Shouts to all the members at solidsurf.info, particulary to Jack for publicizing my map.

This is a combat/linear surf I made.

You start off on a glass platform floating in the sky. It Breaks. You fall down onto the surf and you surf to get guns. People who fall in jail get a knife and a he grenade. After some amount of time you are released back onto the surf. The higher you surf the better guns you get. Lots of weird surfing and other stuff, so yeah, have fun and don't forget to kill people.

Hello,
  This is an update to the map surf_antimatter. I replaced all of the textures with Nyro's dev textures. After I saw a version that Sync made, I was spurred on to retexture the map. The colors are mostly the same so that map has the same aesthetic, but the new textures provide more feedback to the surfer. 

  I believe this is a better version since it does not diminish the original, but enhances it. If you are unaffected by the problems many people had with the original textures, then you will remain unaffected. However, if you felt like the original textures didn't give you enough feedback while surfing, then hopefully this version will solve those problems for you.

Big thanks to Sync for helping me, FalseLogic for the test server, and Nyro for the textures. Give it a try and tell me what you think. As always, I hope you enjoy it!
